<title>JAPAN: Investors sell Sega due to unclear future.</title>
<headline>Investors sell Sega due to unclear future.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-04-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Sega Enterprises Ltd fell to a low for the year on Monday afternoon as investors sold the shares due to doubts about the future profitability of the company after it merges with Bandai Co Ltd, brokers said.</p>
<p>As of 0436 GMT, the shares were down 150 yen at 2,870.  </p>
<p>&quot;There are no new developments to bring on selling of Sega shares, but in the video game industry it is widely believed that Sony Corp and Nintendo Co Ltd are going to reign at the top of the industry,&quot; a trader at a medium-sized brokerage said.</p>
<p>&quot;There is some hope that Sega's merger with Bandai will help shrink the gap between it and the leaders, but the merits of the merger are still unclear and are not supportive factors for the share price,&quot; he added.</p>
